  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Sean Hollister\" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"36\" height=\"36\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" srcset=\"https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/author_profile_images/196092/sean-nerf-profile-pic..0.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=48 1x, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/author_profile_images/196092/sean-nerf-profile-pic..0.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=96 2x\" src=\"https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/author_profile_images/196092/sean-nerf-profile-pic..0.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=96\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/authors/sean-hollister\"\u003eSean Hollister\u003c/a\u003e \u003cspan\u003eis a senior editor and founding member of The Verge who covers gadgets, games, and toys. He spent 15 years editing the likes of CNET, Gizmodo, and Engadget.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"zephr-anchor\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eWill Sony ever release a remake or remaster of \u003cem\u003eBloodborne\u003c/em\u003e, the\u003cem\u003e Dark Souls\u003c/em\u003e successor that became one of \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2015/12/21/10633178/bloodborne-best-video-game-2015-playstation-4\"\u003eour favorite games of 2015\u003c/a\u003e? Even Sony’s former games chief \u003ca href=\"https://www.ign.com/articles/why-hasnt-sony-done-anything-more-with-bloodborne-playstation-legend-shuhei-yoshida-has-a-personal-theory\"\u003eisn’t sure\u003c/a\u003e — but that isn’t stopping Sony’s copyright enforcers from shutting down fun in the meanwhile. Last week, \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/news/604239/sony-bloodborne-60-fps-mod-removal-dmca-takedown-lance-mcdonald\"\u003eit axed the 60fps mod\u003c/a\u003e that let the game finally run smoothly, and now it’s killed the fan-made “Bloodborne PSX” demake that reimagined \u003cem\u003eBloodborne\u003c/em\u003e as a block game for the original 1995 PlayStation.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eIt’s been over three years since Lilith “b0tster” Walther \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/1/31/22910985/bloodborne-psx-demake-pc-fangame\"\u003ereleased her homage to early PlayStation games\u003c/a\u003e, and it’s only now that Sony is taking it down — or rather MarkScan, the enforcer that slapped the game with \u003ca href=\"https://itch.io/takedowns/1370201\"\u003ea copyright takedown notice\u003c/a\u003e that \u003ca href=\"https://b0tster.itch.io/bbpsx\"\u003ehas now taken over its itch.io page\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eHere’s a copy of the copyright takedown notice for posterity; it claims that Walther is engaging in “digital piracy.”\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971,0,91.728155339806,100\" data-pswp-height=\"1181\" data-pswp-width=\"944.8000000000001\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"“Dear Madam/Sir,We MarkScan, represent Sony Interactive Entertainment,“ the notice begins. \" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=256 256w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=376 376w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=384 384w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=415 415w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=480 480w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=540 540w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=640 640w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=750 750w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=828 828w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=1080 1080w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=1200 1200w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=1440 1440w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=1920 1920w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/takedown-notice-bloodborne-psx.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=4.1359223300971%2C0%2C91.728155339806%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eIt’s not surprising that Sony wouldn’t want Walther to promote her work using its copyrighted names, and the company’s almost certainly within its rights to wait a few years before doing so. What’s surprising is that Sony needed an enforcer in the first place; Walther was happy to change \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/3/25/22996465/bloodborne-kart-psx-demake\"\u003eher other “Bloodborne Kart” game\u003c/a\u003e to “Nightmare Kart” \u003ca href=\"https://www.pcgamer.com/bloodborne-kart-wont-be-bloodborne-kart-anymore-after-a-letter-from-sony-but-the-devs-are-excited-to-make-it-an-original-thing-this-is-a-fan-game-no-more/\"\u003eafter Sony simply reached out and asked her.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eBut maybe that’s because MarkScan is playing whack-a-mole on Sony’s behalf. MarkScan was \u003cem\u003ealso\u003c/em\u003e the one behind the \u003cem\u003eBloodborne\u003c/em\u003e 60fps mod takedown, \u003ca href=\"https://x.com/manfightdragon/status/1887328055536066885?s=46\u0026amp;t=0kj2sx3_wl7cRwN6sAu8xg\"\u003esays mod creator Lance McDonald\u003c/a\u003e, and it also took down one of Walther’s YouTube videos about \u003cem\u003eBloodborne PSX \u003c/em\u003ewith a copyright claim.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0,0,100,100\" data-pswp-height=\"558\" data-pswp-width=\"592\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=256 256w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=376 376w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=384 384w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=415 415w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=480 480w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=540 540w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=640 640w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=750 750w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=828 828w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1080 1080w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1200 1200w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1440 1440w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1920 1920w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/lance-mcdonald-tweet.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eMarkScan submits millions upon millions of URL takedown requests on behalf of Sony, Amazon, Netflix, Crunchyroll, Novi Digital Entertainment and more, \u003ca href=\"https://transparencyreport.google.com/copyright/reporters/43177?request_by_owner=size:10;org:43177;p:MTpBTExfVElNRTozOjQzMTc3OjEwOjA6MTA\u0026amp;lu=request_by_owner\u0026amp;hl=en\"\u003eaccording to a Google transparency report\u003c/a\u003e; Google winds up removing around 47 percent of them.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhy go after these videos now? That’s what I’d like to know. Sony did get our hopes up by putting \u003cem\u003eBloodborne\u003c/em\u003e at the very end of \u003ca href=\"https://youtu.be/KkmonzpHVRg?si=5m9hFT-gghPNFhAJ\u0026amp;t=113\"\u003eits 30th Anniversary thank-you video\u003c/a\u003e in December with the words “It’s about persistence” — could it be a coded message to fans that they need to keep on waiting?\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0,0,100,100\" data-pswp-height=\"550\" data-pswp-width=\"774\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"“It’s about persistence” displays over video of Bloodborne’s main character fighting with a jagged cleaver like sword.\" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=256 256w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=376 376w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=384 384w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=415 415w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=480 480w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=540 540w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=640 640w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=750 750w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=828 828w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1080 1080w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1200 1200w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1440 1440w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1920 1920w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/image-28.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ccite\u003eImage: Sony\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eHere’s hoping this isn’t the beginning of a “demake” purge, as they’re a delightful and creative way to remix games; I doubt they substantially reduce the demand for true remakes.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
